  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Class 4 Hooklift Driver",
  "description": "<p><em><strong>Job Duties &amp; Responsibilities :</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Driving a hooklift truck to perform Open Top Container deliveries and pick-ups in accordance with the schedule and in a safe, professional, and timely manner.</li>\n  <li>Filling in service/ delivery order forms.</li>\n  <li>Performing and recording daily checks.</li>\n  <li>Performing and recording minor maintenance tasks such as greasing, fluid top-ups, etc.</li>\n  <li>Washing the truck and cleaning the interior.</li>\n  <li>Other work required to complete waste disposal jobs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Class 4 driving license</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of relevant working experience in the Waste Management (Environmental Services)</li>\n  <li>With WSQ Certificate of Transport Waste during Waste Collection will be advantageous</li>\n  <li>Professional attitude towards driving vehicle</li>\n  <li>Be reliable, punctual and motivated with a strong work ethic</li>\n  <li>Able to work 6 days per week</li>\n  <li>Pls call Ms Cindy @ 9630 1556</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Job Benefits</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Good remuneration package including medical benefits and performance bonus</li>\n  <li>Training and learning opportunities</li>\n</ul>",
